06056nam a22009255i 9789048550654DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20202020ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485506547 a10.1515/97890485506542doi  a(DE-B1597)550718  a(OCoLC)1204256147  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 7aHIS0370102bisacsh04a282.09222300aCardinal Adam Easton (c. 1330-1397) :bMonk, Scholar, Theologian, Diplomat /ced. by Miriam Wendling. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (228 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aChurch, Faith and Culture in the Medieval West00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tPreface -- tAbbreviations -- tFigures and Examples -- tIntroduction -- t1. Adam Easton and the Great Schism -- t2. The Dating and Origin of Cambridge, Corpus Christi College, MS 180 : Adam Easton’s copy of Richard FitzRalph’s De pauperie Salvatoris -- t3. Adam Easton and the Lutterworth Wall Paintings Revisited -- t4. Easton and Dante: beyond Chaucer -- t5. Adam Easton and St Birgitta of Sweden: a remarkable affinity -- t6. Adam Easton’s Office for the Feast of the Visitation of the Virgin Mary -- t7. Between Tradition and Innovation : the sepulchral monument of Adam Easton at S. Cecilia in Trastevere -- t8. Adam Easton’s Manuscripts -- tIndex -- tIndex of Manuscripts0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe varied career of Adam Easton (c. 1330-1397) led him from Norwich Cathedral Priory to Oxford, Avignon and Rome. Not only a monk of the Benedictine Order, he was also a scholar, theologian, diplomat and cardinal, and his work reflects the breadth of this multifaceted background. This volume presents recent research on Easton's oeuvre, his diplomacy, and the books that accompanied him on his travels. Amongst the works addressed in this volume are Easton's Defensorium ecclesiastice potestatis, his Defensorium S. Birgittae and his Office for the Feast of the Visitation. Further new evidence is also offered on his testimony during the Great Schism, on the dating of his copy of De pauperie Salvatoris, while two reassessments are made of his likeness, including his sepulchral monument at S. Cecilia in Rome and the Lutterwork wall painting. Finally, a catalogue of Easton's important manuscript collection is also provided.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCardinalszEnglandvBiography. 0aDeans, Cathedral and collegiatezEnglandzYorkvBiography. 4aHigh Middle Ages. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aInternational Relations. 4aReligion and Theology. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  amedieval manuscripts, papal curia, Great Schism, religious reform, Saint Birgitta.1 aBolgia, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDennison, Lynda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGill, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHavely, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutchison, Ann M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWendling, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWendling, Miriam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZutshi, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G